[Outbreaks of human salmonellosis related to fish for eating are uncommon and are more likely to be related to contamination of the fish after they are caught. A central location with continued contamination of the outbreak strain would be needed for the outbreak to continue over 2+ months since the storability of the fish is quite limited. It is more likely that, if the sushi continues to be implicated, another ingredient in the sushi such as a spice, a vegetable, or seaweed wrapping would be the vehicle. - Mod.LL]
